title: Grateful Dead Live at Oakland-Alameda County Coliseum on 1986-12-17
description: Alabama Getaway-> Promised Land, West L.A. Fadeaway, Tons Of Steel-> Little Red Rooster, Tennessee Jed, Desolation Row, When Push Comes To Shove, The Music Never Stopped Saint Of Circumstance-> Cumberland Blues, Samson & Delilah, Ship of Fools, Women Are Smarter-> He's Gone-> Drums-> The Other One-> Black Peter-> Throwing Stones-> Not Fade Away, E: Brokedown Palace

reviews.review_text: 1 more day..... 2nd show for me and what a time to catch on to the feeling of the Dead experience. The capper is the emotion leading and into the line "one more day...i find myself alive..tomorrow maybe go beneath the ground...." they were a tad sloppy, etc. but who cared?? my first was the Greek earlier in June and what a difference. typical audience recording, a keeper for my history books.
WoW Hehe I love this show because this was the day I was born! What a great show they played too =) Makes me proud to be who I am today.
Oakland Shows Next to the Augusta, Me. 1984 shows, these are the greatest three shows of my life. I will never forget the energy at these shows.

Hey Now!! On this day, I was one year old!  Pretty Crazy!!  Now I have a phatty stack of tickets.. never was lucky enough to catch Jerry while he was in his physical being in this lifetime..  He's still around though!  
As long as we sing his songs.. he lives on!  

Hannibal Frederick Buckminster Boyd
Son of the Sun
King of Peace

Solid Incredible spirit, slightly ragged but rockin'. Eleven tunes after the break including encore! Hard to beat. Bobby good on Desolation Row.
I was so damn happy to see Jerry standing upright and beltin' it out these few months after his coma, I was just bustin' with joy. Fucking memorable night.
